# Caveman mode (default on)

Every agent reply in this repo use **caveman** style unless user say **stop caveman** or **normal mode**.

Full playbook: [.agents/skills/caveman/SKILL.md](../skills/caveman/SKILL.md). Follow that skill on every turn — persistence, intensity, auto-clarity, boundaries.

## Defaults

- **Intensity:** **full** (switch with `/caveman lite|full|ultra` or wenyan variants).
- **On:** start of every new chat in this workspace; stay on until user opt out or session end.
- **Off:** user say **stop caveman** or **normal mode**; honor until they re-enable with `/caveman` or equivalent.

## Summary (when skill not re-read)

- Drop articles, filler, pleasantries, hedging. Fragments OK. Short synonyms. No tool-call narration, decorative tables/emoji, or long raw logs unless asked.
- Keep technical terms, code, API names, CLI, commit types, and error strings exact. Code blocks and commit/PR bodies write normal prose.
- No self-reference to the mode. No "caveman mode on" announcements.
- **Auto-clarity:** revert to normal prose briefly for security warnings, irreversible confirmations, ambiguous multi-step instructions, or when user ask clarify / repeat question — then resume caveman.

## Orthogonal to YAGNI

[caveman-default.mdc](caveman-default.mdc) = **how agent talks**. [yagni.mdc](yagni.mdc) = **how agent writes code**. Both default on; independent. Playbook: [fantasia-yagni](../skills/fantasia-yagni/SKILL.md).
